article.headline: Oral Roberts 79, Pacific 63
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Dominique Morrison scored 23 of his 29 points in the second half to lead Oral Roberts to a 79-63 win over Pacific in a BracketBuster game on Saturday night. The Golden Eagles (15-14) led 33-30 at halftime, but were never threatened after starting the second half with a 16-6 run. Steven Roundtree added 12 points and Damen Bell-Holter 11 for Oral Roberts, which won its sixth straight. Nyika Williams led the Tigers (15-11) with 18 points, and Allen Huddleston had 13.
